      {
        "title": "PreTweet",
        "description": "PreTweet is a web application that uses crowdsourcing to determine how audiences will respond to a potential tweet. We realized that companies and celebrities frequently publish tweets that do not resonate with their fans for a number of reasons. In the worst cases, these tweets can be very costly for the user. For this reason, we saw a business opportunity to screen the tweets before they are ever released to the public. The application was written in Python and uses the CrowdFlower API to poll users across the world to find out how appropriate, humorous, and grammatically correct a specific tweet is.",
        "duration": "Oct 2014 - Present",
